Ask HN: Service to Facilitate Selling Shares in a Private Company
text:
Does anyone here have a suggested service to do the legal paper work for me to sell some of my shares in a private company? I already have a buyer who is an accredited investor willing to purchase, and I've read the paperwork to know that this is allowed by my company's stock plan (the only thing the company has is the right to buy shares I want to sell at a higher price than my buyer).

Equity Zen and Forge Global are often recommended, but are unwilling to help in this case (they are insisting that we go through their secondary market and can't guarantee that I will sell to my specific buyer, they want to get a larger cut of the transaction, etc.). They are also saying that they need my company's CEO's permission as well, which I know isn't true (based on speaking to past employees).

I'm guessing this isn't a commonly advertised service, but there are probably lawyers who are capable of doing this. If anyone can point such a service out to me, that would be greatly appreciated!
